\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 3. M. hybrida} (Pourret) Trautv., {\i  Bull. Sci. Acad. Imp. Sci. Pétersb.}{\b  8}: 271 (1841) ({\i  M. pourretii} Noulet). Glabrous perennial 10-40 cm. Leaflets broadly obovate to suborbicular, crenulate-serrate; stipules ½-ovate, sagittate, dentate, acute. Racemes 2- to 5-flowered. Legume oblong-falcate, acuminate, dehiscent; transverse veins forming a strong, more or less isodiametric network. Seeds 2-3. {\i  Woods and mountain slopes; calcicole. • Corbieres and Pyrenees.} Ga.
